article.description: Keon Clergeot scored 20 points as UMass rolled past Central Connecticut 89-43 on Saturday.
article.headline: Clergeot carries UMass over Central Connecticut 89-43
article.linkText: Clergeot carries UMass over Central Connecticut 89-43
article.story: AMHERST, Mass. -- Keon Clergeot scored 20 points as UMass rolled past Central Connecticut 89-43 on Saturday. Sean East II had 15 points and six assists for UMass (4-0), which shot 52. 5 % from the floor (32 of 61) and 10 of 22 from behind the 3-point arc. Samba Diallo added 13 points. Djery Baptiste had 12 rebounds and three blocks for the Minutemen. Greg Outlaw had 12 points for the Blue Devils (0-4), who were hampered by 16 of 48 shooting and 24 turnovers. UMass matches up against Rider at home on Wednesday. Central Connecticut looks for its first win against New Hampshire at home on Tuesday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
